CAPE TOWN - Some of the country’s top musos are doing their bit to encourage wise water ways in the drought-stricken Cape Town. They're literally singing to save water by remixing their top-selling songs into just enough time for you to have a shower responsibly. As we know, singing in the shower is a favourite pastime for many –  so here's your chance to do it responsibly. * eNCA’s Tanya Nefdt caught up with some of the artists, showering to their own tune. eNCA